ign:left;mso-line-height-alt:25.5px;"><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0p=
x;">On Monday morning, I was driving home from a short ski trip in Vermont =
when I tapped the
YouTube TV app on my phone to listen in on CNN=E2=80=99s coverage of the <s=
trong>Trump </strong>II inaugural. The kids were in the backseat with their=
 iPads and headphones=E2=80=94a brand-safe environment, you might say, for =
my wife and me to overhear <strong>Jake Tapper </strong>and <strong>Dana Ba=
sh </strong>narrating the unfolding history. Cruising down an unspectacular=
 stretch of I-87, just south of Albany, we exchanged glances as Bash noted =
yet another anomaly of this Boschian<strong>
</strong>portrait of modern American life: a cohort of tech billionaires ta=
king their seats next to Trump=E2=80=99s family=E2=80=94<em>in front</em> o=
f his incoming cabinet, the very people managing his administration. Someho=
w, it made perfect sense.</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=
=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">Silicon Valley=E2=80=99s ga=
me of footsie with the president=E2=80=94particularly the overtures of <str=
ong>Sam Altman</strong>, <strong>Mark Zuckerberg</strong>, and <strong>Elon
Musk</strong>=E2=80=94have been endlessly chewed over yet somehow largely u=
nder-explored. Is it possible that they=E2=80=99re all secret Trumpers with=
 deeply held views on issues like immigration? Possibly, but I=E2=80=99d su=
rmise that they=E2=80=99re also calculating <em>realpolitik </em>executives=
 in charge of hundreds of thousands of employees and businesses whose marke=
t caps, combined, are in the multi-trillions of dollars. So it=E2=80=99s al=
so possible that they have strong views about the future of TikTok, the reg=
ulation of
artificial intelligence, or the impact of policies, like tariffs, on their =
long-term business plans.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;"=
>=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">And, yes, it=E2=80=99s =
<em>also</em> possible that their guts and manifold advisors have suggested=
 that Trump will be at the peak of his powers for the first 18 months of hi=
s regime, before the reality of the midterms, the Constitution, and the sel=
f-interest of House members <em>complexifies</em>, to steal
<strong>Bezos</strong>=E2=80=99s coinage, the political hand he=E2=80=99s b=
een dealt. According to this theory, now would seem to be the best time for=
 them to throw their weight around or simply smile before the camera and ke=
ep their inner thoughts, whatever they may be, to themselves while they tra=
nsact. (The best negotiations, after all, are the ones that don=E2=80=99t l=
ook like negotiations=E2=80=A6) Indeed, the popular assessment of this dyna=
mic posits that Trump is completely using these guys, but what if the relat=
ionship is reciprocal
and they=E2=80=99re all just playing a much longer game?</p><p style=3D"mar=
gin:0;margin-bottom:0px;"><br/>Anyway, I won=E2=80=99t pretend to be able t=
o read anyone=E2=80=99s mind, but even Trump=E2=80=99s short-term political=
 calculus seems a bit suspicious. As <strong>Peter Hamby </strong>notes in =
his excellent piece <a href=3D"https://email.puck.news/e/c/eyJlbWFpbF9pZCI6=
ImRnVDJ4Z1lEQUt2UktxclJLZ0dVbmJXRXN0TjdrTWJJY3RnTTRFYz0iLCJocmVmIjoiaHR0cHM=
6Ly9wdWNrLm5ld3MvdHJ1bXAtdGhlLXBvcHVsaXN0LW5vdy13aXRoLTEwMC1wZXJjZW50LW1vcm=
UtYmlsbGlvbmFpcmVzLz91dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249VGhlK0JhY2tzdG9yeSstK1NVQlNDUklCRVJTK=
yUyODElMkYyNSUyRjI1JTI5XHUwMDI2dXRtX2NvbnRlbnQ9VGhlK0JhY2tzdG9yeSstK1NVQlND=
UklCRVJTKyUyODElMkYyNSUyRjI1JTI5XHUwMDI2dXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbF9hY3Rpb25cdTA=
wMjZ1dG1fc291cmNlPWN1c3RvbWVyLmlvXHUwMDI2dXRtX3Rlcm09ZjZjNjA2MTdkYTQyYWJkMT=
JhIiwiaW50ZXJuYWwiOiJmNmM2MDYxN2RhNDJhYmQxMmEiLCJsaW5rX2lkIjoyMDQ4OTE3fQ/80=
9f9d652f026e72cdbf8c3e2167ada122c3fca3bf2cf32850ad7716643f80b4" style=3D"te=
xt-decoration:underline;color:#d40000;"><em>Trump=E2=80=99s Billionaire Arb=
itrage</em></a>, the optics of the inaugural weren=E2=80=99t
just uncomfortable for his billionaire pals=E2=80=94they were also a misint=
erpretation of the so-called mandate that his sweeping election afforded hi=
m. =E2=80=9CCan Trump plausibly claim to be standing up to powerful tech ov=
erlords and moneyed interests when every photo and camera angle shows him s=
urrounded by America=E2=80=99s private sector royalty?=E2=80=9D Peter persp=
icaciously noted. =E2=80=9CThought about another way: Trump has always deri=
ved his power from running <em>against</em> enemies=E2=80=94hated elites an=
d the establishment.
But who do you run against when you win so bigly that your enemies just giv=
e up and join your team?=E2=80=9D<br/><br/></p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-=
bottom:0px;">The following day, I=E2=80=99d find out that my patronage of C=
NN was, itself, an outlier. As our partner <strong>Dylan Byers </strong>exp=
lained in his latest masterstroke, <a href=3D"https://email.puck.news/e/c/e=
yJlbWFpbF9pZCI6ImRnVDJ4Z1lEQUt2UktxclJLZ0dVbmJXRXN0TjdrTWJJY3RnTTRFYz0iLCJo=
cmVmIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly9wdWNrLm5ld3MvY25ucy15ZWFyLW9mLW1hZ2ljYWwtdGhpbmtpbmcvP3V=
0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1UaGUrQmFja3N0b3J5Ky0rU1VCU0NSSUJFUlMrJTI4MSUyRjI1JTJGMjUlMj=
lcdTAwMjZ1dG1fY29udGVudD1UaGUrQmFja3N0b3J5Ky0rU1VCU0NSSUJFUlMrJTI4MSUyRjI1J=
TJGMjUlMjlcdTAwMjZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsX2FjdGlvblx1MDAyNnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9Y3Vz=
dG9tZXIuaW9cdTAwMjZ1dG1fdGVybT1mNmM2MDYxN2RhNDJhYmQxMmEiLCJpbnRlcm5hbCI6ImY=
2YzYwNjE3ZGE0MmFiZDEyYSIsImxpbmtfaWQiOjIwNTMwMjB9/6f1a89ea4ac931f38bedf44ee=
83a8926d71ff002144e3fe1140c5c1587173d53" style=3D"text-decoration:underline=
;color:#d40000;"><em>The Contracting News Network</em></a>, CNN=E2=80=99s c=
overage of the inaugural
averaged less than <em>one-fifth </em>of the audience it had driven during =
<strong>Biden</strong>=E2=80=99s coronation a mere four years earlier. Betw=
een 11:30 a.m. and 1 p.m. ET on Monday, only 1.7 million people were watchi=
ng CNN, down from 10 million in 2021.</p><p style=3D"margin:0;"><br/>In man=
y ways, CNN would steal the news cycle from Trump shortly after the inaugur=
ation, as C.E.O. <strong>Mark Thompson </strong>confessed to the <em>Times =
</em>what Dylan had reported in Puck three months ago=E2=80=94that
the company will shed hundreds of jobs while it invests in hiring more than=
 100 <em>new</em> employees to architect its digital future. It=E2=80=99s a=
n uncertain plan, but no one has a better idea. Dylan captures the nuances =
of this strategy, and there are many of them, in his excellent follow-up, <=
a href=3D"https://email.puck.news/e/c/eyJlbWFpbF9pZCI6ImRnVDJ4Z1lEQUt2Uktxc=
lJLZ0dVbmJXRXN0TjdrTWJJY3RnTTRFYz0iLCJocmVmIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly9wdWNrLm5ld3MvY25u=
cy1sYXlvZmZzLWhhdmUtYmVndW4td2hhdC1uZXh0Lz91dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249VGhlK0JhY2tzdG9=
yeSstK1NVQlNDUklCRVJTKyUyODElMkYyNSUyRjI1JTI5XHUwMDI2dXRtX2NvbnRlbnQ9VGhlK0=
JhY2tzdG9yeSstK1NVQlNDUklCRVJTKyUyODElMkYyNSUyRjI1JTI5XHUwMDI2dXRtX21lZGl1b=
T1lbWFpbF9hY3Rpb25cdTAwMjZ1dG1fc291cmNlPWN1c3RvbWVyLmlvXHUwMDI2dXRtX3Rlcm09=
ZjZjNjA2MTdkYTQyYWJkMTJhIiwiaW50ZXJuYWwiOiJmNmM2MDYxN2RhNDJhYmQxMmEiLCJsaW5=
rX2lkIjoyMDU4MDc4fQ/74323e65dcdbe0222637de3a89c9dbdfb25d7f1fea3451cb40d18b6=
3e6a15046" style=3D"text-decoration:underline;color:#d40000;"><em>CNN After=
 CNN</em></a>.<br/><br/>Indeed, the news has never been more complicated, a=
nd the way we
receive it has never been more balkanized, and yet both matter more than ev=
er. These are the stories of our time, and precisely what you should expect=
 to read in Puck.</p></div>
